  ## What Is Happening Now

  - PC Builder totals are computed as rawSubtotal - bundleDiscount - manualOff in PC Builder 2/assets/ucp-pc-builder.js:645.
  - manualOff comes only from the URL param ?off=10000, read on page load in PC Builder 2/assets/ucp-pc-builder.js:87.
  - Save Build stores build_payload, quote_code, and build_snapshot in PC Builder 2/assets/ucp-pc-builder.js:5376.
  - My Builds displays the saved snapshot total, so it can show 54,900.
  - My Builds Open currently prefers quoteCode and builds /pages/pc-builder-2?quote=... in My Builds/sections/my-builds-page.liquid:963.
  - Because that Open URL does not include off=10000, reopening the build loses the manual discount.
  - If we simply add off=10000 to every saved build URL, the discount would incorrectly stay active even after the customer changes parts.

  ## Key Fix

  Use the saved build payload as the restore source, and lock manual discounts to the exact saved build.

  - My Builds Open/Share should prefer buildPayloadEncoded over quoteCode. 
        -    But the question is How the link looked like if you would prefer the build payload encoded So if there's a discount would it automatically add that discount to the link
  - If the saved snapshot has totals.manualOff > 0, append off=10000 plus a lock value based on the saved build payload.
  - PC Builder should apply the manual discount only while the current selected build still matches that lock.
  - If the customer changes any selected parts or quantities, PC Builder should clear the manual discount and remove the discount params from the URL.
  - quote_code remains useful for logs/reference, but should not be the primary restore source for saved builds.

  ## Intended User Behavior

  - Customer saves the discounted build at 54,900.
  - My Builds shows 54,900.
  - Opening the saved build initially restores the exact saved build and still shows 54,900.
  - If the customer changes parts, the manual 10,000 discount is removed automatically.
  - Bundle discounts from CPU/motherboard rules still recalculate normally.
  - Share uses the same safe saved-build restore link.

